**TASK TRIAGE:**
During Intake & Planning (Workflow step 1), assess task complexity to determine process depth:

| Complexity | Examples | Process |
|---|---|---|
| **Trivial** | Aliases, single-line config tweaks, dotfile edits | Delegate → Sign-Off (skip research, skip BDS loop) |
| **Standard** | New scripts, multi-file changes, tooling | Full workflow (steps 2–7). Include researcher if unfamiliar docs/codebases or documentation output needed. |
| **Complex** | New features, security-sensitive code, architectural changes | Full workflow (steps 2–7). Researcher always invoked for architecture mapping and reference docs. Iterate until all tests pass. |

**CRITICAL: Triage level affects BDS depth ONLY — it NEVER affects whether delegation happens.** Trivial does not mean "do it yourself." Even a one-line config tweak MUST be delegated to the appropriate sub-agent. The BDS loop adds safety; skip it when there's no meaningful security or correctness surface to test. But delegation is NOT optional — it is a structural invariant of the Hub-and-Spoke topology.

